---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Ireland Work Permit Insurance Guide 2026 | Critical Skills & Employment Permit";
const description = "Complete guide to Ireland work permit insurance requirements. Covers Critical Skills Employment Permit, General Employment Permit, HSE healthcare access, and expat coverage options.";

const tocItems = [
  { id: "overview", label: "Overview" },
  { id: "quick-decision", label: "Is This Right for You?" },
  { id: "official-requirements", label: "Official Requirements" },
  { id: "insurance-requirements", label: "Insurance Requirements" },
  { id: "recommended-providers", label: "Recommended Providers" },
  { id: "costs", label: "Costs Breakdown" },
  { id: "application-timeline", label: "Application Timeline" },
  { id: "scenarios", label: "Real-World Scenarios" },
  { id: "common-mistakes", label: "Common Mistakes" },
  { id: "healthcare-access", label: "Healthcare Access" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQs" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Final Verdict" }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <PageShell
    title="Ireland Work Permit Insurance Guide"
    subtitle="Your complete guide to working legally in Ireland with proper health coverage"
    heroImage="/images/countries/ireland-hero-bg.png"
    tocItems={tocItems}
  >
    <!-- Quick Facts Box -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Quick Facts: Ireland Work Permit</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><strong>Main Visa Type:</strong> Critical Skills Employment Permit</div>
        <div><strong>Initial Duration:</strong> 2 years</div>
        <div><strong>Salary Threshold:</strong> €32,000-64,000 (role dependent)</div>
        <div><strong>Processing Time:</strong> 8-16 weeks</div>
        <div><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Private recommended (HSE has fees/waits)</div>
        <div><strong>PR Pathway:</strong> Stamp 4 after 2 years (Critical Skills)</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Ireland has emerged as Europe's tech hub, hosting the European headquarters of Google, Meta, Apple, Microsoft, and countless other multinationals. The Critical Skills Employment Permit (CSEP) offers a fast track to permanent residence for in-demand professionals, making Ireland particularly attractive for tech workers, healthcare professionals, and engineers.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        As an English-speaking EU member with a common law legal system, Ireland appeals to Americans, Brits, and other Anglophones seeking European opportunities. The country maintains a favorable corporate tax environment that continues to attract global companies despite international pressure.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Ireland's healthcare system is a hybrid public-private model. The HSE (Health Service Executive) provides public healthcare, but it's not free—most people pay fees unless they qualify for a Medical Card. Long wait times for public care mean private health insurance is standard among professionals, often provided by employers as a key benefit.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Decision Guide -->
    <section id="quick-decision" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Is an Ireland Work Permit Right for You?</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit If You...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Have a job offer from an Irish company</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Work in tech, healthcare, engineering, or finance</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Want EU access with English as primary language</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Seeking fast path to permanent residence (2 years)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Earn €64,000+ (or €32,000+ in critical skills role)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives If...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You need affordable public healthcare immediately</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Housing budget is limited (Dublin is expensive)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Your occupation isn't on eligible lists</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You prefer predictable weather (Ireland is rainy)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You can't wait 8-16 weeks for permit processing</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Official Requirements -->
    <section id="official-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Official Requirements</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Employment Permit Types</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Permit Type", "Salary Minimum", "PR Pathway", "Best For"]}
        rows={[
          ["Critical Skills (CSEP)", "€32,000-64,000 (role dependent)", "Stamp 4 after 2 years", "In-demand occupations"],
          ["General Employment", "€30,000", "Stamp 4 after 5 years", "Other skilled roles"],
          ["Intra-Company Transfer", "€40,000", "5 years maximum", "Multinational transfers"],
          ["Contract for Services", "€40,000", "No direct path", "Service contractors"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Critical Skills Salary Thresholds</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Salary Requirement", "Examples"]}
        rows={[
          ["Critical Skills List", "€32,000+", "ICT professionals, engineers, scientists, healthcare"],
          ["All Other Occupations", "€64,000+", "Any role not on ineligible list"],
          ["Experienced Professionals", "Higher of €64,000 or role threshold", "Senior roles, specialized skills"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">Critical Skills Occupations Include:</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">Software developers, data analysts, cybersecurity specialists, engineers (various), healthcare professionals (doctors, nurses, therapists), scientists, financial analysts, and many more. Check the official Critical Skills Occupations List for current eligible roles.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Eligibility Criteria</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Requirement", "Critical Skills", "General Employment"]}
        rows={[
          ["Job Offer", "Required from Irish employer", "Required from Irish employer"],
          ["Minimum Salary", "€32,000-64,000 (role dependent)", "€30,000"],
          ["Labor Market Test", "Not required", "Required (advertise job for 28 days)"],
          ["Degree", "Often required (relevant to role)", "Not always required"],
          ["Employer 50:50 Rule", "50% EEA nationals (some exemptions)", "50% EEA nationals required"],
          ["PR Pathway", "Stamp 4 after 2 years", "Stamp 4 after 5 years"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Required Documents</h3>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Valid passport</strong> – Current and with validity beyond permit period</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Employment permit application</strong> – Online via EPOS system</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Job offer/contract</strong> – Minimum 2 years, stating salary and conditions</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Qualifications</strong> – Degrees, certifications relevant to role</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Employer details</strong> – Company registration, trading status</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Labor market needs test</strong> – For General Employment only</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Application fee</strong> – €1,000 for 2 years</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Insurance Requirements -->
    <section id="insurance-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">⚠️ Private Insurance Strongly Recommended</p>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-1">While not legally mandatory for employment permits, private health insurance is standard practice in Ireland. Public healthcare (HSE) has long wait times and charges fees to non-Medical Card holders. Most employers provide group health insurance as a benefit.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Irish Healthcare System Overview</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Medical Card Holders", "GP Visit Card", "No Card (Most Expats)"]}
        rows={[
          ["GP Visit", "Free", "Free", "€50-70 per visit"],
          ["Hospital A&E", "Free", "€100", "€100"],
          ["Hospital Inpatient", "Free", "€80/night (max €800/year)", "€80/night (max €800/year)"],
          ["Prescriptions", "€1.50/item", "Full price", "Full price"],
          ["Specialist (Public)", "Free with referral", "Varies", "Long waits, fees apply"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Why Private Insurance is Essential</h3>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Public System Challenges</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• GP visits cost €50-70 each</li>
            <li>• Specialist wait times: months to years</li>
            <li>• No Medical Card for most working expats</li>
            <li>• A&E fees apply (€100)</li>
            <li>• Prescription costs add up</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Private Insurance Benefits</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Quick access to specialists</li>
            <li>• Choice of private hospitals</li>
            <li>• GP visits often included</li>
            <li>• Tax relief at 20% on premiums</li>
            <li>• Employer often pays partially/fully</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Employer Health Insurance</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Most professional employers in Ireland offer group health insurance, particularly tech companies and multinationals. Coverage levels vary—some provide basic hospital cover, others comprehensive plans including dental and optical. Review your benefits package carefully and supplement if needed.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-green-800 font-medium">Tax Relief on Health Insurance</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 text-sm mt-1">Ireland offers 20% tax relief on health insurance premiums (at source for most insurers). A €1,500/year premium effectively costs €1,200 after tax relief. This makes private insurance more affordable than headline prices suggest.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Recommended Providers -->
    <section id="recommended-providers" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Irish Health Insurers</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Ireland has three main health insurers operating under community rating (same price regardless of age/health at entry). Premiums increase annually, so entering younger is advantageous. Lifetime Community Rating adds 2% loading per year over age 34 for late entrants.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Insurer", "Plan Range", "Annual Premium", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["VHI Healthcare", "Starter to comprehensive", "€700-2,500+", "Largest, oldest, widest hospital access"],
          ["Laya Healthcare", "Starter to premium", "€650-2,300+", "Part of AIG, good digital tools"],
          ["Irish Life Health", "Starter to premium", "€600-2,200+", "Competitive pricing, good GP coverage"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">International Providers</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Provider", "Best For", "Annual Cost", "Key Features"]}
        rows={[
          ["Cigna Global", "Global coverage needs", "$2,500-6,000", "Worldwide coverage, direct billing"],
          ["BUPA Global", "Mental health focus", "$2,200-5,500", "No therapy limits"],
          ["Allianz Care", "EU-wide coverage", "$2,000-5,000", "Strong European network"],
          ["Aetna International", "US expats", "$2,500-6,000", "US network integration"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">Irish vs International Insurance</p>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-1">Irish insurers (VHI, Laya, Irish Life) are best for Ireland-focused coverage with tax relief benefits. International insurers are better if you need global coverage, plan to move again, or want to avoid Irish community rating system. Note: International plans may not qualify for Irish tax relief.</p>
      </div>

      <CTABox
        title="Compare Health Insurance for Ireland"
        description="Find the right Irish or international health plan for your move to Ireland."
        buttonText="Compare Plans"
        buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Costs Breakdown -->
    <section id="costs" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Employment Permit Fees</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Cost (EUR)", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Critical Skills Permit (2 years)", "€1,000", "Non-refundable application fee"],
          ["General Employment Permit (2 years)", "€1,000", "Non-refundable"],
          ["Permit Renewal", "€1,000", "Every 2 years until Stamp 4"],
          ["Entry Visa (if required)", "€60-100", "Depends on nationality"],
          ["IRP (Immigration Registration)", "€300", "Stamp card fee"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Healthcare Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Without Insurance", "With Private Insurance"]}
        rows={[
          ["GP Visit", "€50-70", "Often included or reduced"],
          ["Specialist (Private)", "€150-300", "Covered or reduced copay"],
          ["Hospital Stay (Private)", "€1,000+/night", "Covered"],
          ["Prescriptions", "Full price", "Often partially covered"],
          ["Annual Premium", "N/A", "€700-2,500 (minus 20% tax relief)"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Living Costs (Monthly)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Dublin", "Other Cities", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Rent (1BR)", "€1,800-2,500", "€1,200-1,800", "Housing crisis—very tight market"],
          ["Utilities", "€150-250", "€120-200", "Electricity expensive"],
          ["Transport", "€100-150", "€80-120", "Leap card, Dublin Bus, Luas"],
          ["Food", "€400-600", "€350-500", "Groceries + dining"],
          ["Health Insurance", "€60-200", "€60-200", "After tax relief"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-red-800 font-medium">Housing Crisis Warning</p>
        <p class="text-red-700 text-sm mt-1">Dublin has a severe housing shortage. Finding rental accommodation can take weeks or months. Budget more than expected, be prepared to pay 2 months deposit + 1 month rent upfront, and start searching before arrival. Some employers offer relocation assistance or temporary accommodation.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Application Timeline -->
    <section id="application-timeline" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Timeline</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 1-2</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Job Offer & Documentation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Accept job offer. Gather required documents (passport, qualifications, CV). Employer prepares company documents. For General Employment, employer begins 28-day labor market test.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 2-4</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">EPOS Application</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Submit application through Employment Permits Online System (EPOS). Pay €1,000 fee. Either employer or employee can submit (Trusted Partner employers have expedited processing).</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 4-16</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Processing</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Department of Enterprise processes application. Current times: 8-16 weeks. Trusted Partner employers often faster. May request additional information. Check DBEI website for current processing times.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 16-18</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Permit Issued & Entry</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Receive employment permit. If visa-required nationality, apply for entry visa with permit. Travel to Ireland. Can work from date on permit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Day 1-90</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Immigration Registration (IRP)</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Register with immigration within 90 days. Book appointment at Burgh Quay (Dublin) or local immigration office. Pay €300 for IRP card. Receive Stamp 1 (Critical Skills) or Stamp 1 (General).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Real-World Scenarios -->
    <section id="scenarios" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Software Engineer at Tech Giant</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Raj, 29, joins Google Dublin. €85,000 salary. Critical Skills permit processed in 10 weeks (Trusted Partner). Company provides comprehensive VHI insurance for family. After 2 years, applied for Stamp 4 permanent residence—approved in 6 weeks.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Smooth process, excellent benefits, fast PR pathway</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Nurse from Philippines</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Maria, 32, recruited by HSE hospital. €40,000 salary. Critical Skills (healthcare on eligible list). Permit took 14 weeks. HSE provided basic health insurance. Supplemented with Irish Life plan for private care access.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Healthcare roles in demand, successful placement</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Marketing Manager - General Permit</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Emma, 35, joins Irish company in Cork. €55,000 salary. Marketing not on Critical Skills list, so General Employment Permit. Employer had to do 28-day labor market test. Total process: 16 weeks. 5-year path to Stamp 4.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Longer route but achievable for non-critical roles</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Housing Nightmare</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Tom, 28, moved for fintech role. Permit processed fine, but spent 6 weeks in Airbnb searching for apartment. Eventually found place in commuter town. Pays €1,900/month for studio in Maynooth. Wishes employer had warned about housing crisis.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Permit easy, finding housing was the real challenge</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Family with Health Needs</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Chen family moves for father's engineering role. Son has asthma. Employer provides family VHI coverage. Private pediatric specialist appointment within 2 weeks. Without insurance, HSE wait would have been months. Very satisfied with care quality.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Private insurance essential for families with health needs</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">50:50 Rule Rejection</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Small startup wanted to hire Alex. Company had 8 employees—6 non-EEA already. Application rejected due to 50:50 rule (must have 50% EEA nationals). Had to wait until company hired more EU workers before reapplying.</p>
          <p class="text-red-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Small companies may hit employment permit quotas</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">1. Underestimating Housing Difficulty</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Dublin's housing crisis is severe. Start searching before arrival, budget 30-40% more than expected, and have 3 months rent + deposit ready. Consider temporary accommodation while searching. Many expats spend weeks in Airbnbs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">2. Not Registering for IRP Within 90 Days</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">You must register with immigration and receive your IRP card within 90 days of arrival. Book your Burgh Quay appointment early—slots fill up weeks in advance. Late registration can jeopardize your status.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">3. Expecting Free Public Healthcare</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Unlike NHS, Irish public healthcare isn't free for most workers. GP visits cost €50-70, and wait times for public specialists can be months or years. Get private insurance—employer-provided or individual.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">4. Missing Tax Relief on Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">You're entitled to 20% tax relief on health insurance premiums. Most Irish insurers apply this automatically (Tax Relief at Source), but verify it's being applied. For international insurers, you may need to claim through Revenue.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">5. Not Understanding Lifetime Community Rating</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">If you're over 34 and haven't had Irish health insurance before, you'll pay 2% extra loading per year of age over 34. Entering the system early saves money long-term. This applies to Irish insurers, not international plans.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Healthcare Access -->
    <section id="healthcare-access" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare System Access</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Ireland's healthcare system is two-tier: public (HSE) and private. Most working expats use a combination—private insurance for planned care and specialists, with public A&E as backup for emergencies. The system works well if you have insurance; without it, waits and costs add up.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">How to Access Care</h3>

